=====注=====
:<sup>{{note|1|A}}</sup> [[National_Olympic_Committee|NOC]] was not member of [[国际奥林匹克委员会|IOC]]
:<sup>{{note|2|B}}</sup> as {{flagicon|ROC}} China from 1936–56
:<sup>{{note|3|C}}</sup> part of {{flagicon|YUG}} Yugoslavia from 1936–1988
:<sup>{{note|4|D}}</sup> part of {{URS}}
:<sup>{{note|5|E}}</sup> as {{flagicon|FRG}} West Germany from 1968–88
:<sup>{{note|6|F}}</sup> part of {{flagIOC|EUN}} in 1992
:<sup>{{note|7|G}}</sup> now {{flagicon|SRB}} Serbia, part of {{YUG}} in 1936–1988, as {{flagIOCteam|IOP|1992 Summer}} in 1992 and part of {{FR-YUG}} in 1996–2000
:<sup>{{note|8|H}}</sup> part of {{SCG}} in 2004
:<sup>{{note|9|I}}</sup> part of {{flagicon|MAS}} Malaysia in 1964
:<sup>{{note|10|J}}</sup> Soviet Union chose not to compete in 1936 and 1948
:<sup>{{note|11|K}}</sup> part of {{flagicon|TCH}} Czechoslovakia from 1920–92

